China is the world's largest jailer of cyber-dissidents, with 52 individuals imprisoned for online activities deemed inappropriate by the Communist Party.
Reporters Without Borders warns that other countries are following suit, potentially leading to a global internet model of censorship and surveillance.
Recent attacks on internet root servers highlight the growing threat of cybercrime, with hackers using botnets to commit crimes on a massive scale.
The need for enhanced internet security measures is evident, as criminals exploit vulnerabilities to steal data and disrupt online activities.
The challenge lies in staying ahead of evolving cyber threats to safeguard the integrity of the internet.
